        <h1>Privacy Policy for Annadanam Finder</h1>
        <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> December 2024</p>
        
        <section>
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>Annadanam Finder ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application ("App"). Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use the App.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            
            <h3>2.1 Information You Provide to Us</h3>
            <p>We collect information that you provide directly to us, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When you create an account or sign in, we may collect:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Email address (if you sign in with Google or Apple)</li>
                        <li>Phone number (if you choose to provide it)</li>
                        <li>Display name and profile photo (if you choose to provide them)</li>
                        <li>Authentication tokens from third-party providers (Google Sign-In, Sign in with Apple)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Contribution Data:</strong> When you contribute to our directory, we collect:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Temple/ashram/spiritual center information (name, address, GPS coordinates)</li>
                        <li>Meal timings and availability information</li>
                        <li>Photos you upload to verify locations</li>
                        <li>Notes and additional details about locations</li>
                        <li>Your contributor name (if you choose to display it)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>User Interactions:</strong> We collect:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Search queries and filters you use</li>
                        <li>Confirmations when you receive Annadanam</li>
                        <li>Upvotes, downvotes, and reports you submit</li>
                        <li>Feedback and reports about locations</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
            <p>When you use our App, we automatically collect certain information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Device Information:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Device type, model, and manufacturer</li>
                        <li>Operating system version</li>
                        <li>Unique device identifiers (such as device ID, advertising ID)</li>
                        <li>App version and installation information</li>
                        <li>Language preferences</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Location Data:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your current GPS location (only when you grant permission)</li>
                        <li>Location data is collected only when:
                            <ul>
                                <li>You search for nearby locations</li>
                                <li>You add a new location (to auto-fill the address)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>We do NOT continuously track your location in the background</li>
                        <li>You can revoke location permissions at any time through your device settings</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>App usage patterns and features accessed</li>
                        <li>Session duration and frequency of use</li>
                        <li>Search history and preferences</li>
                        <li>Errors and crashes (for app improvement)</li>
                        <li>Performance metrics</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Network Information:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>IP address</li>
                        <li>Network type (Wi-Fi, cellular)</li>
                        <li>Connection quality</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>To Provide and Maintain Our Service:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Enable you to search for Annadanam locations</li>
                        <li>Allow you to contribute new locations</li>
                        <li>Provide navigation and mapping features</li>
                        <li>Maintain your account and preferences</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>To Improve Our Service:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve app functionality</li>
                        <li>Fix bugs and errors</li>
                        <li>Develop new features</li>
                        <li>Personalize your experience</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>To Ensure Quality and Safety:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Verify the accuracy of contributed locations</li>
                        <li>Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, or spam</li>
                        <li>Moderate user-generated content</li>
                        <li>Respond to reports and feedback</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>To Communicate with You:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Send important service updates</li>
                        <li>Respond to your inquiries</li>
                        <li>Provide customer support</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>To Comply with Legal Obligations:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Comply with applicable laws and regulations</li>
                        <li>Respond to legal requests</li>
                        <li>Protect our rights and the rights of our users</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>4. Location Data</h2>
            <div class="highlight">
                <p><strong>Important:</strong> We take your location privacy seriously.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>We collect your location <strong>ONLY with your explicit permission</strong></li>
                    <li>Location data is used <strong>SOLELY</strong> for:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Finding nearby Annadanam locations when you search</li>
                            <li>Auto-filling location information when you add a new place</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>We <strong>DO NOT</strong> track your location continuously or in the background</li>
                    <li>We <strong>DO NOT</strong> share your precise location with third parties</li>
                    <li>You can revoke location permissions at any time through your device settings</li>
                    <li>If you revoke location permissions, you can still use the app by manually entering locations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We <strong>DO NOT sell, trade, or rent</strong> your personal information to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>
            <p>We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>
            
            <h3>5.1 Public Contributions</h3>
            <p>When you contribute a location, the following information becomes publicly visible to all app users:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Temple/ashram name and address</li>
                <li>GPS coordinates (for mapping purposes)</li>
                <li>Meal timings and details</li>
                <li>Photos you upload</li>
                <li>Your contributor name (if you choose to display it)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This information is necessary for the app's core functionality.</p>
            
            <h3>5.2 Service Providers</h3>
            <p>We use third-party service providers to help us operate our App. These providers have access to your information only to the extent necessary to perform their services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Google Firebase:</strong> Authentication, database (Firestore), file storage, analytics, crash reporting, and remote configuration</li>
                <li><strong>Google Maps Platform:</strong> Mapping, geocoding, and location services</li>
                <li><strong>Google Places API:</strong> Address autocomplete and place details</li>
                <li><strong>Google ML Kit:</strong> Text recognition from images (processed on-device)</li>
                <li><strong>Apple (for iOS users):</strong> Sign in with Apple authentication</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These service providers are bound by their own privacy policies and terms of service.</p>
            
            <h3>5.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
            <p>We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Valid legal requests (subpoenas, court orders)</li>
                <li>Government investigations</li>
                <li>Protection of our rights, property, or safety</li>
                <li>Protection of the rights, property, or safety of our users</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>5.4 Business Transfers</h3>
            <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            
            <h3>6.1 Data Storage</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Your data is stored securely on <strong>Google Firebase (Google Cloud Platform)</strong></li>
                <li>Data is encrypted in transit using HTTPS/TLS</li>
                <li>Data is encrypted at rest on Google's servers</li>
                <li>Data is stored in servers located in regions determined by Google Cloud</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>6.2 Data Retention</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We retain your account data as long as your account is active</li>
                <li>Contribution data (temple listings) is retained to maintain the directory</li>
                <li>You can request deletion of your account and associated data (see Section 8)</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>6.3 Security Measures</h3>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encrypted data transmission (HTTPS)</li>
                <li>Secure authentication mechanisms</li>
                <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
                <li>Regular security assessments</li>
                <li>Secure coding practices</li>
            </ul>
            <p>However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>7. Third-Party Services and SDKs</h2>
            <p>Our App uses the following third-party services and SDKs:</p>
            
            <h3>7.1 Google Services</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Firebase Authentication:</strong> User authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Cloud Firestore:</strong> Database storage</li>
                <li><strong>Firebase Storage:</strong> Photo and file storage</li>
                <li><strong>Firebase Analytics:</strong> Usage analytics (anonymized)</li>
                <li><strong>Firebase Crashlytics:</strong> Crash reporting</li>
                <li><strong>Firebase Remote Config:</strong> App configuration</li>
                <li><strong>Google Maps SDK:</strong> Maps and location services</li>
                <li><strong>Google Places API:</strong> Address autocomplete</li>
                <li><strong>Google ML Kit:</strong> On-device text recognition</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Google Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></p>
            
            <h3>7.2 Apple Services (iOS)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Sign in with Apple:</strong> Authentication for iOS users</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Apple Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.apple.com/privacy/</a></p>
            
            <h3>7.3 Other Services</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Image Picker:</strong> Access to device camera and photo library</li>
                <li><strong>Location Services:</strong> GPS and location services</li>
                <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device identifiers and system information</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These third-party services have their own privacy policies and terms of service. We encourage you to review them.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
            
            <h3>8.1 Access</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can access your account information through the App settings</li>
                <li>You can view your contributions and activity</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>8.2 Correction</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can update your account information through the App</li>
                <li>You can edit or remove your contributions</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>8.3 Deletion</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can request deletion of your account and associated data</li>
                <li>To request deletion, contact us at the email address provided in Section 13</li>
                <li>Note: Public contributions (temple listings) may remain visible to maintain the directory, but will be anonymized</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>8.4 Location Data</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can opt-out of location tracking by revoking location permissions in your device settings</li>
                <li>You can still use the app by manually entering locations</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>8.5 Analytics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Firebase Analytics collects anonymized usage data</li>
                <li>You cannot opt-out of analytics, but the data is anonymized and aggregated</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>8.6 Account Deletion</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can delete your account through the App settings</li>
                <li>Upon account deletion:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your account information will be deleted</li>
                        <li>Your contributions will be anonymized (removed from your account but may remain in the directory)</li>
                        <li>Some data may be retained for legal or operational purposes</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>9. Anonymous Usage</h2>
            <p>You can use the App with <strong>anonymous authentication</strong> (guest mode). In this mode:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We collect minimal data necessary for app functionality</li>
                <li>We do not require email or phone number</li>
                <li>Location data is still collected if you grant permission (for search functionality)</li>
                <li>Usage analytics are still collected (anonymized)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Our App is <strong>not intended for children under the age of 13</strong> (or the minimum age required by law in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from those in your country. By using our App, you consent to the transfer of your information to these countries.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any material changes by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Posting the updated Privacy Policy in the App</li>
                <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
                <li>For significant changes, we may provide additional notice through the App</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Your continued use of the App after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.</p>
        </section>
        
